${project.name}

  This plugin manages the ability to start/stop the JBoss Application Server
  and to deploy/undeploy files to the JBoss Application Server.

  The plugin requires an existing installation of the 
  {{{http://www.jboss.org/jbossas/}JBoss AS}}.  If one is not already available,
  it can be downloaded from the 
  {{{http://www.jboss.org/jbossas/downloads/}JBoss AS downloads page}}.

* Goals Overview
  
  The following goals are available in this plugin.
  
  * <<<{{{./configure-mojo.html}jboss:configure}}>>>\
    Configure a JBoss Server.

  * <<<{{{./start-mojo.html}jboss:start}}>>>\
    Start a JBoss Server.

  * <<<{{{./start-and-wait-mojo.html}jboss:start-and-wait}}>>>\
    Start a JBoss Server and wait for startup to complete.

  * <<<{{{./stop-mojo.html}jboss:stop}}>>>\
    Shutdown a running JBoss Server.

  * <<<{{{./deploy-mojo.html}jboss:deploy}}>>>\
    Deploy a file or directory to JBoss using JMX.

  * <<<{{{./undeploy-mojo.html}jboss:undeploy}}>>>\
    Undeploy a file or directory to JBoss using JMX.

  * <<<{{{./redeploy-mojo.html}jboss:redeploy}}>>>\
    Redeploy a file or directory to JBoss using JMX.

  * <<<{{{./hard-deploy-mojo.html}jboss:hard-deploy}}>>>\
    Deploy a file or directory to JBoss by copying files directly to the server deployment directory.

  * <<<{{{./hard-undeploy-mojo.html}jboss:hard-undeploy}}>>>\
    Undeploy a file or directory to JBoss by removing files from the server deployment directory.

* Usage

